<subSubSection pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1437,151,679]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,333,512,536]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named in honor James N. Zahniser, 
<collectingRegion box="[906,985,511,535]" country="United States of America" name="Illinois" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Illinois</collectingRegion>
Natural History Survey, for his work on the phylogeny of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1825" box="[347,490,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cicadellidae</taxonomicName>
, particularly his treatise of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dallas" authorityYear="1870" box="[955,1141,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Deltocephalinae">Deltocephalinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1437,151,679]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,584,608]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
From 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nielson" authorityYear="1982" box="[388,550,584,608]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Docalidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis box="[388,408,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[422,550,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nielson" box="[564,787,583,607]" firstAuthor="Nielson" page="300" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="289 - 320" refId="ref55387" refString="Nielson, M. W. (1982 h) New species of leafhoppers of Docalidia from Peru (Cicadellidae: Coeldiinae, Teruliini). Entomography, 1, 289 - 320." type="journal article" year="1982" yearSuffix="h">Nielson, 1982h:300</bibRefCitation>
) to which it is similar in pygofer and style features, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicName authority="Nielson, 2011" authorityName="Nielson" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Docalidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zahniseri" status="sp. nov.">zahniseri</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[207,298,620,644]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[207,298,620,644]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished by the presence of distal setae and absence of medial spine on the apophysis of the style, and the more robust, twisted aedeagal shaft.
</paragraph>
